sequenceDiagram
    participant Agent as AI Agent<br/>(Claude Desktop/Code)
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS Edge
    participant MCP as RHOAI MCP Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Auth as Auth System<br/>(OIDC/TokenReview)
    participant RBAC as RBAC Filter<br/>(SubjectAccessReview)
    participant Plugin as Domain Plugin<br/>(pluggy)
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry<br/>8080/8443 TCP
    participant Planner as Planner Backend<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant GitHub as GitHub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Agent,K8s: Flow 1: MCP Tool Invocation (Kubernetes Operation)
    Agent->>Route: SSE/HTTP POST<br/>Bearer Token (optional)
    Route->>MCP: HTTP 8000/TCP<br/>TLS terminated at edge
    MCP->>Auth: Validate token
    alt OIDC Mode
        Auth->>Auth: JWT validation via JWKS
        Auth->>K8s: SubjectAccessReview
        K8s-->>Auth: allowed/denied
    else Token Mode
        Auth->>K8s: TokenReview API
        K8s-->>Auth: user identity
    end
    Auth-->>MCP: UserContext set via contextvars
    MCP->>RBAC: Filter tools by user permissions
    RBAC->>K8s: SubjectAccessReview per tool
    K8s-->>RBAC: permission results
    RBAC-->>MCP: visible tools list
    MCP->>Plugin: Execute tool handler
    Plugin->>K8s: CRUD via dynamic client<br/>Impersonate-User headers (OIDC mode)
    K8s-->>Plugin: API response
    Plugin-->>MCP: Structured result
    MCP-->>Route: MCP JSON response
    Route-->>Agent: HTTPS response

    Note over Agent,ModelReg: Flow 2: Model Registry Query
    Agent->>Route: MCP tool call:<br/>list_registered_models
    Route->>MCP: HTTP 8000/TCP
    MCP->>Plugin: Model Registry plugin
    Plugin->>ModelReg: GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>httpx async client
    ModelReg-->>Plugin: JSON model list
    Plugin-->>MCP: Structured result
    MCP-->>Route: MCP response
    Route-->>Agent: Models & versions

    Note over Agent,GitHub: Flow 3: Quickstart Deployment
    Agent->>Route: MCP tool call:<br/>deploy_quickstart
    Route->>MCP: HTTP 8000/TCP
    MCP->>Plugin: Quickstart plugin
    Plugin->>GitHub: git clone<br/>rh-ai-quickstart repo
    GitHub-->>Plugin: Repository contents
    Plugin->>Plugin: helm install / oc apply
    Plugin->>K8s: Create resources<br/>(Deployment, Service, etc.)
    K8s-->>Plugin: Resources created
    Plugin-->>MCP: Deployment status
    MCP-->>Route: MCP response
    Route-->>Agent: Quickstart deployed

    Note over Agent,MCP: Workflow Token Flow
    Agent->>MCP: prepare_training(params)
    MCP->>Plugin: Validate prerequisites
    Plugin->>K8s: Check namespace, storage, runtime
    K8s-->>Plugin: All prerequisites met
    Plugin-->>MCP: Result + HMAC workflow_token
    MCP-->>Agent: {result, workflow_token: "hmac..."}
    Agent->>MCP: create_training_job(workflow_token)
    MCP->>Plugin: Verify HMAC token (stateless)
    Plugin->>K8s: Create TrainJob CR
    K8s-->>Plugin: TrainJob created
    Plugin-->>MCP: Job status
    MCP-->>Agent: Training job submitted
